headline: MTD Q1 Earnings Call: Tariffs, Supply Chain Shifts, and Margin Mitigation Take Center Stage
summary: Precision measurement company Mettler-Toledo (NYSE:MTD) reported Q1 CY2025 results beating Wall Street’s revenue expectations, but sales fell by 4.6% year on year to $883.7 million. Its non-GAAP profit of $8.19 per share was 3.9% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
